diagnostic_tests_recommended.expected_findings: Hypoxemia (low PaO2), possible metabolic acidosis (low pH, decreased bicarbonate), elevated anion gap if diabetic ketoacidosis is present.

diagnostic_tests_recommended.expected_findings: Electrolyte disturbances (e.g., hyperkalemia or hypokalemia), elevated BUN and creatinine indicating dehydration or renal impairment.
